.TH JIRA2MD 1 "March 2026" "work2md 0.9.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
jira2md \- export Jira issues to Markdown
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B jira2md
.I ISSUE_KEY_OR_URL
[\fB\-\-output-dir\fR \fIPATH\fR]
[\fB\-\-stdout\fR]
[\fB\-\-emit\fR \fITARGET\fR]
[\fB\-\-ai-friendly\fR]
[\fB\-\-front-matter\fR]
[\fB\-\-redact\fR \fIRULES\fR]
[\fB\-\-drop-field\fR \fIFIELDS\fR]
[\fB\-\-incremental\fR]
[\fB\-\-log-format\fR \fITEXT_OR_JSON\fR]
[\fB\-\-input-file\fR \fIPATH\fR]
[\fB\-\-jql\fR \fIQUERY\fR]
[\fB\-\-version\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B jira2md
exports a Jira issue to Markdown.
It stores user-specific configuration in
.I ~/.config/work2md/config
and writes Markdown output to
.I ./docs/jira/
by default.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-output-dir PATH
Write the generated output bundle to the given directory.
.TP
.B \-\-stdout
Print one generated artifact to standard output instead of writing files.
.TP
.B \-\-emit TARGET
Select the stdout artifact to print. Supported values are
.BR index ,
.BR metadata ,
and
.BR comments .
.TP
.B \-\-ai-friendly
Create an additional AI-friendly export variant with a linearized content layout.
.TP
.B \-\-front-matter
Prepend YAML front matter to the generated
.IR index.md .
.TP
.BI "\-\-redact " RULES
Redact one or more comma-separated classes such as
.BR email ,
.BR account-id ,
or
.BR internal-url .
.TP
.BI "\-\-drop-field " FIELDS
Remove one or more comma-separated metadata fields before writing
.I metadata.md
and generated front matter.
.TP
.B \-\-incremental
Consult and update
.I manifest.json
so unchanged export bundles can be skipped on later runs.
.TP
.BI "\-\-log-format " text|json
Select plain text or JSON formatted log output on stderr.
.TP
.BI "\-\-input-file " PATH
Read issue keys or Jira URLs from a file and export them in sequence.
.TP
.BI "\-\-jql " QUERY
Resolve a Jira issue list from a JQL query and export the matching issues.
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Show usage information.
.TP
.B \-V, \-\-version
Show the installed version.
